# Kysely Lane Boundary

## Preserve lane ownership

- `db.kysely` in `@prisma-next/postgres` must expose the lane-owned surface from `@prisma-next/sql-kysely-lane`, not raw `Kysely` types from the composition root.
- Keep Kysely-specific composition internals (build-only dialect/driver, redaction marker behavior, lane helper plumbing) inside the lane package.

## Keep build-only semantics explicit

- Public types must not expose execution methods (`execute*`, `stream*`, `transaction*`) on `db.kysely` or lane-authored query handles.
- Runtime backstop must remain deterministic for cast/`any` bypass attempts.

## ORM interop boundary

- ORM `.where(...)` accepts `WhereArg` only (`WhereExpr | ToWhereExpr`).
- Use lane helper output (e.g. `db.kysely.whereExpr(...)`) for Kysely-authored filter interop; do not pass full `SqlQueryPlan` into `.where(...)`.
